&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;GENERAL FUNCTION&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a &lt;strong&gt;Lead Software Engineer, Backend &amp;amp; Cloud Platform&lt;/strong&gt;, to help own and operate Integration Hub, an AWS-based integration platform supporting Integration with Internal &amp;amp; External systems. You’ll work across backend services (APIs, event-driven processing), data synchronization and file ingestion pipelines, and production operations. A key part of this role is supporting the transition of production support from our current vendor to an internal team, including knowledge transfer, runbooks, and establishing sustainable operational practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;DUTIES/RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and evolve backend API services built with Node.js / NestJS running on AWS ECS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement event-driven patterns using Kafka (AWS MSK) and caching with Redis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and enhance file ingestion pipelines using S3, Lambda, schedulers, and Python/Node.js components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve data sync workloads (e.g., AWS Batch/Lambda, scheduled jobs), ensuring correctness and recoverability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead/participate in on-call and incident response, including post-incident RCAs and preventive improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve CI/CD and engineering quality: GitHub Actions, Jest, performance testing (e.g., k6), static analysis/security scanning (e.g., SonarQube, Veracode).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage infrastructure changes via Terraform, including networking (e.g., NLB), observability, and runtime configuration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Business stakeholders and partner teams on requirements, SLAs, and release planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vendor transition &amp;amp; operational readiness:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the vendor team to drive structured knowledge transfer (architecture deep dives, incident walkthroughs, deployment procedures).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain runbooks, support playbooks, and troubleshooting guides for APIs, ingestion, and sync processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish internal operational practices: alert tuning, dashboards, on-call processes, escalation paths, and post-incident RCA discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and reduce vendor dependencies (scripts, access, undocumented procedures), ensuring the internal team can operate independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support a parallel-run period where internal engineers progressively take ownership of L1/L2/L3 support with vendor as fallback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;EXPERIENCE &amp;amp; EDUCATION&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in computer science or equivalent amount of experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of software engineering experience, with strong backend development expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Node.js experience.&lt;/li&gt;
